txt.en: 'This means more than you know. I'll see to it that my fellows' belongings are treated with care.\n\n'Thank you.'
You have retrieved a number of belongings from fallen hunters at Dor Pherkha.\n\nYou should venture north-west to Kafagur and bring what you've collected to the hunter Rúkbag.

The bodies of fallen Kafagur hunters lie scattered around Dor Pherkha. A number of them must hold personal effects, as well as salvageable equipment. It might be worth reclaiming such items and returning them to Kafagur.
Retrieve belongings from fallen hunters at Dor Pherkha
Fallen hunters can be found around Dor Pherkha.\n\nYou should retrieve their belongings.
It might be worth reclaiming the fallen hunters' belongings and returning them to Kafagur.
The bodies of fallen Kafagur hunters lie scattered around Dor Pherkha.
